{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"The I\/O Kit is a set of system frameworks and libraries for creating device drivers on Mac OS X, supporting both 32 and 64 bit architectures. Learn about the design of I\/O Kit drivers, as well as tips and tricks for fast, efficient driver development and debugging. Whether you’re bringing a new device to Mac OS X or developing an application to access an existing device, this session is for you.","type":"text"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/203\/","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","type":"reference"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC10","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"I\/O Kit Device Drivers for Mac OS X"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-203-io-kit-device-drivers-for-mac-os-x"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-203-IO-Kit-Device-Drivers-for-Mac-OS-X"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC10":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10","title":"WWDC10","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC10-Ico